HEADWORD: Cross-reading
<hw>Cross"-read`ing</hw> <pr>(r?d`?ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
reading of the lines of a newspaper directly across the page, instead of
down the columns, thus producing a ludicrous combination of
ideas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

